                  <persName id="t18240603-49-person459">
                  EDMUND 
                  MORTON HILL
               <interp inst="t18240603-49-person459" type="surname" value="MORTON HILL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-49-person459" type="given" value="EDMUND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-49-person459" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18240603-49-viclabel256" type="occupation">coach-master</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240603-49-victim458 t18240603-49-viclabel256"></join>. I was at <placeName id="t18240603-49-crimeloc257">No. 15, Finsbury-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240603-49-crimeloc257" type="placeName" value="No. 15, Finsbury-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240603-49-crimeloc257" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240603-49-off254 t18240603-49-crimeloc257"></join>, on the 20th of May, waiting for a family to take to Holloway - I had a blue box-coat on the coach-box - two persons asked me the way to Wood-street, and to Finsbury-street - I missed the coat the moment I gave the answer.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>JOHN M'LANE. I was in Finsbury-square, and saw the prisoner with a blue coat under his arm, talking to a man - when he saw me he ran away, and dropped it - I am positive as to his person - the manner in which he held the coat made me think he had not got it honestly - I followed him and picked it up, and then lost sight of him - I saw him again that evening, at the watch-house - he was dressed the same as when I saw him - he was not charged with taking the coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-49-person460">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CROSS
               <interp inst="t18240603-49-person460" type="surname" value="CROSS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-49-person460" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-49-person460" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol - I heard a cry of Stop thief! and saw the prisoner running away - I followed and took him - I don't know who gave the alarm - I saw M'Lane that night at the watch-house - he said that is the person I saw throw the coat away - the prisoner replied, that he had not seen the coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-49-person461">
                  CHARLES 
                  RICKETS
               <interp inst="t18240603-49-person461" type="surname" value="RICKETS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-49-person461" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-49-person461" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable - M'Lane gave me the coat on the 20th of May.</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was passing through Finsbury-square and saw a crowd, and I passed through to see what was the matter - soon after an officer seized me.</p>

               <p>
                  <rs id="t18240603-49-verdict258" type="verdictDescription">
